WEBVTT

00:01.080 --> 00:03.830
Dre: Christmas has always been
the favorite holiday

00:03.830 --> 00:05.250
in the Johnson house.

00:05.250 --> 00:07.830
It's the holiday that
brings out the best in us.

00:07.830 --> 00:10.170
♪ Hey, playa,
whatcha gonna get, punk ♪

00:10.170 --> 00:12.000
♪ For Christmas? ♪
♪ Yeah! ♪

00:12.000 --> 00:13.290
♪ Whatcha gonna get ♪

00:13.290 --> 00:15.960
Well, sometimes it brings out
the best in us.

00:15.960 --> 00:18.670
We have lots
of family traditions,

00:18.670 --> 00:21.380
but Pops only has one...

00:21.380 --> 00:23.460
Well, we go through this
every year, Earl.

00:23.460 --> 00:25.500
We close at 6:00 p.m.
on Christmas Eve.

00:25.500 --> 00:27.000
It's Christmas Eve
again?

00:27.000 --> 00:28.670
Yes.
Already?

00:28.670 --> 00:31.000
...which sucked
when I was a kid,

00:31.000 --> 00:32.830
but over time
it's been one of the things

00:32.830 --> 00:34.170
I've gotten used to.

00:34.170 --> 00:36.080
Pops just doesn't
do Christmas.

00:36.080 --> 00:37.880
[ Horn honks "Jingle Bells" ]
[ Laughs ]

00:37.880 --> 00:39.830
What's that?

00:39.830 --> 00:41.830
Merry Christmas, family!

00:41.830 --> 00:43.000
-Oh!
-Whoa!

00:43.000 --> 00:45.420
Lynette: We lost a few gifts
on the freeway,

00:45.420 --> 00:47.420
but there's something
for everyone!

00:47.420 --> 00:48.330
[ Laughs ]

00:48.330 --> 00:49.670
Ooh!

00:49.670 --> 00:51.080
What the hell?

00:56.120 --> 00:58.000
What gives, Pops?

00:58.000 --> 00:59.420
Huh?
I thought
you hated Christmas.

00:59.420 --> 01:00.500
Well, in the past,

01:00.500 --> 01:02.500
I never had a reason
for the season.

01:02.500 --> 01:04.250
[ Chuckles ]
Hurtful.

01:04.250 --> 01:05.540
But Lynette
loves Christmas,

01:05.540 --> 01:06.960
and seeing it
through her eyes

01:06.960 --> 01:09.830
has just opened me up
to just how special it is.
Mnh-mnh.

01:09.830 --> 01:11.620
Did you know Starbucks

01:11.620 --> 01:13.080
changes their cups
at Christmas?

01:13.080 --> 01:15.420
Look at this.
The lady's in a snowflake.

01:15.420 --> 01:17.000
Now, how'd they get the lady
in the snowflake?

01:17.000 --> 01:18.710
What you doing
in the snowflake, baby?

01:18.710 --> 01:21.000
How is it that
you are in your 60s

01:21.000 --> 01:22.250
and you are only just now

01:22.250 --> 01:23.670
discovering
the Christmas spirit?
Mm.

01:23.670 --> 01:25.580
I know. I feel like
I've been missing out.

01:25.580 --> 01:27.330
You've been missing out?
[ Chuckles ]

01:27.330 --> 01:29.000
One year you gave me
a piece of coal

01:29.000 --> 01:30.580
and told me
it would be a diamond

01:30.580 --> 01:31.790
if I was stronger.

01:31.790 --> 01:34.170
Well, we'll just have
to make up for lost time.

01:34.170 --> 01:37.040
This year the Johnsons
are going all out.

01:37.040 --> 01:39.790
We're gonna roast chestnuts
on an open fire,

01:39.790 --> 01:41.420
we're gonna deck the halls,

01:41.420 --> 01:43.710
we're gonna put little presents
in them big-ass socks.

01:43.710 --> 01:44.880
What?

01:44.880 --> 01:45.920
Stockings?

01:45.920 --> 01:49.040
Man, they got a name
for all this stuff?

01:49.040 --> 01:51.380
Ooh!
Wow.

01:51.380 --> 01:53.500
I might be
going out on a limb here, son,

01:53.500 --> 01:55.170
but this feels like

01:55.170 --> 01:57.000
the most wonderful time
of the year.

01:57.000 --> 01:59.670
So this is what Alzheimer's
looks like.

01:59.670 --> 02:01.330
Pops, you're pitching
Christmas to us

02:01.330 --> 02:02.500
like it's vegetables.

02:02.500 --> 02:04.460
You've made the sale, brother.
We're in.

02:04.460 --> 02:06.670
Uh, maybe
you should incorporate

02:06.670 --> 02:08.290
some of my traditions,
as well.

02:08.290 --> 02:11.670
Ooh, we really
don't like to stray

02:11.670 --> 02:13.080
from our own traditions.

02:13.080 --> 02:15.080
We're very traditional
like that.

02:15.080 --> 02:16.710
Are you sure?

02:16.710 --> 02:19.290
Because one of the traditions
in my family

02:19.290 --> 02:22.250
is that we hide $200
in the house

02:22.250 --> 02:23.790
on Christmas Eve.

02:23.790 --> 02:28.500
And in the morning,
all of the kids hunt for it.

02:28.500 --> 02:30.250
Can we have a moment,
please?

02:31.330 --> 02:33.000
We're in.

02:33.000 --> 02:35.000
We'd also like to call you
"Nana Nette."

02:35.000 --> 02:37.500
Okay, well,
I'll go get my money.

02:37.500 --> 02:39.790
-Ah.
-[ Laughs ]

02:39.790 --> 02:41.920
Another
Christmas miracle.

02:41.920 --> 02:43.040
Mm, mm.

02:43.040 --> 02:44.120
I got a warm, fuzzy feeling

02:44.120 --> 02:45.540
I thought I could only
get from alcohol.

02:45.540 --> 02:47.290
I'm glad
you've come to embrace

02:47.290 --> 02:50.000
what is easily the most popular
day of the year, Pops.

02:50.000 --> 02:51.830
Dre, I recognize that,
in years past,

02:51.830 --> 02:52.880
I have disappointed,

02:52.880 --> 02:54.290
but that stops now.

02:54.290 --> 02:55.670
What's done is done.
I promise.

02:55.670 --> 02:57.580
Now, you want
to live in the past

02:57.580 --> 02:58.710
or you want to go find

02:58.710 --> 03:01.210
the best damn Christmas tree
in town?

03:01.210 --> 03:03.080
I want to forget the past

03:03.080 --> 03:05.960
and find the best damn
Christmas tree in town.

03:05.960 --> 03:06.960
But, Dad...
Hm?

03:06.960 --> 03:08.420
...we already have a tree

03:08.420 --> 03:10.540
that you and I
picked out together.

03:10.540 --> 03:12.460
Put it in the trash.

03:12.460 --> 03:13.880
Daddy, let's go!

03:13.880 --> 03:16.000
Hurtful.
[ Door closes ]

03:16.000 --> 03:18.920
So, do we have a head count
for the open house yet?

03:18.920 --> 03:20.540
Uh, yeah.

03:20.540 --> 03:23.210
Somewhere between
18 and 48 people.

03:23.210 --> 03:24.500
No one has RSVP'd.

03:24.500 --> 03:27.670
I bet you if Jamie Foxx
was having this party,

03:27.670 --> 03:29.880
people
would have RSVP'd.

03:29.880 --> 03:32.170
But all I get is,
"[Bleep] you, Bow."

03:33.540 --> 03:34.960
You know what?
I'm just --

03:34.960 --> 03:36.380
I'm just gonna go.

03:36.380 --> 03:37.920
Alright. I'm gonna make
the Christmas list.

03:37.920 --> 03:39.330
Alright.

03:39.330 --> 03:42.000
Looks like someone's
having a stressful day.

03:42.000 --> 03:44.330
Oh, God,
you know how it is.

03:44.330 --> 03:48.460
Every year, there's just so much
Christmas to take care of.

03:48.460 --> 03:51.000
Well, I'm pretty handy
in the kitchen.

03:51.000 --> 03:53.210
Are you?
If you're comfortable,

03:53.210 --> 03:56.830
I'd be honored if you'd let me
make Christmas dinner.

04:00.330 --> 04:01.500
There's my list.

04:01.500 --> 04:04.000
Oh, sweetie,
I don't need anything.
Oh.

04:04.000 --> 04:07.620
I'm going to do
my traditional Creole buffet.

04:07.620 --> 04:08.960
Okay.

04:08.960 --> 04:12.500
I'm talking boudin,
étouffée, shrimp remoulade.

04:12.500 --> 04:14.330
Christmas can't get
any better.

04:14.330 --> 04:16.080
Hey!

04:16.080 --> 04:19.330
I'm off for my Silver Singles
Christmas cruise.

04:19.330 --> 04:20.500
[ Chuckles ]

04:20.500 --> 04:22.380
I'll see you suckers
after the ball drops.

04:22.380 --> 04:24.540
[ Chuckles ]
Merry Christmas.

04:24.540 --> 04:27.000
Hey.

04:27.000 --> 04:28.170
Thank you, Santa.

04:28.170 --> 04:31.170
♪ When you never had
a Christmas ♪

04:31.170 --> 04:34.750
♪ Like the ones in TV shows ♪

04:34.750 --> 04:37.000
♪ No good gifts
beneath the tree ♪

04:37.000 --> 04:41.080
♪ No bikes or boxes
tied with bows ♪

04:41.080 --> 04:44.170
♪ But Santa must have
got my letter ♪

04:44.170 --> 04:47.580
♪ Because my Pops
is so much better ♪

04:47.580 --> 04:49.460
♪ Many years
I've waited 'round ♪

04:49.460 --> 04:50.670
Dre: Let's dance.

04:50.670 --> 04:55.830
♪ For Father Christmas
to come to town ♪

04:55.830 --> 04:57.250
♪ Yeah ♪

04:57.250 --> 04:58.330
♪ Father Christmas ♪

04:58.330 --> 05:00.170
♪ So glad you're the man ♪

05:00.170 --> 05:01.420
♪ Father Christmas ♪

05:01.420 --> 05:02.920
♪ With the Christmas plan ♪

05:02.920 --> 05:04.790
♪ 40 years ♪

05:04.790 --> 05:08.210
[ Camera shutter clicking ]
♪ Till Father Christmas
came to town ♪♪

05:08.210 --> 05:12.620
♪ Fa-la-la-la-la-la,
la-la-la-laaaa ♪

05:12.620 --> 05:14.710
[ Chuckles ]
Here's a $50.

05:14.710 --> 05:16.540
Make sure you take care
of everybody.

05:16.540 --> 05:17.830
[ Chuckles ]
Happy holidays.

05:17.830 --> 05:19.330
-Happy holidays.
-Happy holidays.

05:19.330 --> 05:20.710
Uh, ladies like necklaces,
right?

05:20.710 --> 05:22.080
'Cause that's what I got
Lynette.

05:22.080 --> 05:24.830
As long as it doesn't say
"Life Alert," you're fine.

05:24.830 --> 05:25.880
Oh, cool, cool.

05:25.880 --> 05:26.960
[ Both chuckle ]

05:26.960 --> 05:28.040
Hey, kids,

05:28.040 --> 05:29.500
I'm gonna need you
to go get Lynette, Doug,

05:29.500 --> 05:30.830
and the rest of the family,
alright?

05:30.830 --> 05:32.000
We're gonna do
Christmas story.

05:32.000 --> 05:33.620
Ooh.
Okay.
[ Chuckles ]

05:33.620 --> 05:36.830
It was Christmas Eve,
and the house was full of love.

05:36.830 --> 05:38.670
Come on, guys.
Christmas story.

05:38.670 --> 05:41.500
Me and Pops.
Pops and Lynette.

05:41.500 --> 05:43.000
I was even digging Doug...

05:43.000 --> 05:44.290
I'll be right there.

05:44.290 --> 05:46.040
...even though he drank
too much of my Scotch,

05:46.040 --> 05:48.120
and Bow finally got to relax.

05:48.120 --> 05:52.330
Ha. So that's why she got
a dragon tattoo.

05:52.330 --> 05:54.790
I was finally getting
the Christmas

05:54.790 --> 05:56.040
I'd always dreamed of.

05:56.040 --> 05:58.540
[ Laughs ]

05:58.540 --> 06:01.120
Grab your places.
Let's get this story started.

06:01.120 --> 06:03.210
Alright,
come on, everybody!

06:03.210 --> 06:05.000
"Then they opened
their treasures

06:05.000 --> 06:08.580
and presented him with gifts
of gold, frankincense..."

06:08.580 --> 06:09.790
And?
"...and myrrh."

06:09.790 --> 06:10.790
-Myrrh.
-Whoa!

06:10.790 --> 06:12.000
[ Thudding, bells jingle ]

06:12.000 --> 06:13.040
Did you guys hear that?

06:13.040 --> 06:14.250
Huh-unh.
Hear what?

06:14.250 --> 06:15.830
[ Thudding, bells jingle ]
That.

06:15.830 --> 06:17.500
Up on the roof.

06:17.500 --> 06:19.040
[ Thudding and jingling
continues ]

06:19.040 --> 06:20.880
If it's up on the roof,
it can only mean one thing.

06:20.880 --> 06:23.880
Ho, ho, ho,
ho, ho, ho, ho!

06:23.880 --> 06:25.500
Merry Christmas!

06:25.500 --> 06:27.170
Oh, my God!

06:27.170 --> 06:28.540
My elves and I
have been working

06:28.540 --> 06:30.250
to make sure that this

06:30.250 --> 06:33.500
is a Christmas
that no one forgets.

06:33.500 --> 06:37.170
And I have a sack
full of presents

06:37.170 --> 06:41.330
for all the good boys
and girls.

06:41.330 --> 06:42.750
I've been good, Santa.
I want a present.

06:42.750 --> 06:43.960
I've been good.

06:43.960 --> 06:45.170
Oh, ho, ho, ho!
[ Doorbell rings ]

06:45.170 --> 06:47.170
You see what happens
when you tip the carolers?

06:47.170 --> 06:48.920
I'm gonna have them
spread joy elsewhere.

06:48.920 --> 06:50.330
[ Laughter ]

06:52.500 --> 06:54.290
Oh, hey.

06:54.290 --> 06:55.460
Merry Christmas,
brother.

06:55.460 --> 06:56.880
Can -- Can I help you?

06:56.880 --> 06:58.080
Merry Christmas.

06:58.080 --> 06:59.670
Is Lynette here?

06:59.670 --> 07:01.670
Uh, yeah. Come in.

07:01.670 --> 07:04.170
-Thank you.
-Mm-hmm.

07:04.170 --> 07:08.040
Hey, Lynette, uh,
you got a visitor.

07:08.040 --> 07:10.880
[ Gasps ]
Phillip?

07:10.880 --> 07:13.120
-Phillip?
-Oh, my...

07:13.120 --> 07:14.330
Ain't that your ex?

07:14.330 --> 07:16.540
Lynette, when I got back
to Sierra Leone,

07:16.540 --> 07:19.000
I realized I should've
never asked you to --

07:19.000 --> 07:21.330
to choose between me
and your life here.

07:21.330 --> 07:24.670
So I have sold
everything.
[ Gasps ]

07:24.670 --> 07:26.710
Alright,
I'm giving up my life

07:26.710 --> 07:28.080
because I choose you.

07:28.080 --> 07:30.460
Phillip, you should not
have come here.

07:31.710 --> 07:33.670
But I'm so glad you did.

07:33.670 --> 07:35.670
Wait. Lynette. Wait, wait.
Hold up, now. W--

07:35.670 --> 07:37.670
Earl,
when Phillip and I split,

07:37.670 --> 07:40.080
it was because I thought
we could never be together.

07:40.080 --> 07:41.620
What are you saying?

07:41.620 --> 07:45.080
Earl, I'm so sorry.

07:45.080 --> 07:46.580
I love you.

07:48.250 --> 07:50.000
But I need him.

07:52.000 --> 07:54.290
Phillip, did you just
get in tonight?

07:54.290 --> 07:55.540
Phillip:
I flew in last evening.

07:57.580 --> 08:00.670
[ Door closes ]

08:00.670 --> 08:02.500
[ Bells jingle ]

08:02.500 --> 08:04.670
Oh, my God.

08:04.670 --> 08:06.380
So...

08:06.380 --> 08:08.380
I think I'll probably just --

08:08.380 --> 08:10.120
Yeah, I'm just gonna go.

08:10.120 --> 08:17.120
♪♪

08:17.120 --> 08:18.380
[ Door closes ]

08:21.080 --> 08:23.330
There's nothing sadder
than a heartbroken Black man

08:23.330 --> 08:25.210
in a rented Santa suit.

08:25.210 --> 08:28.880
Hey, Pops, I-I don't even
know what to say.

08:28.880 --> 08:32.000
She was the best thing
that ever happened to me.

08:32.000 --> 08:34.620
If you'll excuse me...

08:34.620 --> 08:37.000
[ Bells jingling ]

08:37.000 --> 08:40.460
...I'm gonna go be alone
for a minute.

08:43.380 --> 08:45.170
That poor guy.

08:45.170 --> 08:47.170
I'll go check on him.

08:47.170 --> 08:49.330
Okay, well,
I am gonna be upstairs,

08:49.330 --> 08:51.000
slicing open pillows,

08:51.000 --> 08:52.790
looking for the cash
that Lynette hid.

08:52.790 --> 08:54.000
Hmm.

08:55.620 --> 08:57.460
That homewrecker.

08:57.460 --> 09:00.210
♪♪

09:00.210 --> 09:04.830
♪ Baby,
I believe in this love ♪

09:04.830 --> 09:07.210
♪ Sweet love ♪

09:07.210 --> 09:09.880
♪ Hear me callin' out
your -- ♪

09:09.880 --> 09:11.420
[ Music shuts off ]

09:12.670 --> 09:14.670
Hey.

09:14.670 --> 09:15.710
Are you okay?

09:15.710 --> 09:19.210
Yeah, yeah,
I'm just taking a minute.

09:19.210 --> 09:20.880
[ Sighs ]

09:20.880 --> 09:23.290
Look, you ain't got
to check on me, son.

09:23.290 --> 09:25.580
Go on, enjoy your Christmas.
I'm fine.

09:25.580 --> 09:27.380
Hey, Pops,
it's okay if you're not.

09:27.380 --> 09:28.830
Oh, but I am.

09:28.830 --> 09:29.920
I managed to pour

09:29.920 --> 09:31.460
a whole bottle
of your good Scotch

09:31.460 --> 09:32.540
into this coffee cup,

09:32.540 --> 09:34.210
so I'm-a just hang here.

09:34.210 --> 09:36.330
You go have a nice holiday
with the family.

09:36.330 --> 09:40.170
Pops, I am not about
to leave you out here alone.

09:40.170 --> 09:43.670
Alright, these --
these last few days with you

09:43.670 --> 09:45.790
have been
some of the best,

09:45.790 --> 09:50.170
most Christmasy days
of my life.

09:50.170 --> 09:51.420
Let me pay you back,
Pops.

09:51.420 --> 09:52.920
Let me give you
the best Christmas

09:52.920 --> 09:54.120
that I can give you.

09:54.120 --> 09:57.330
Well,
guess it can't be no worse

09:57.330 --> 10:00.380
than sitting here,
drinking Scotch by myself,

10:00.380 --> 10:03.080
having feelings up to
but not including crying.

10:03.080 --> 10:05.380
Ah, there you go.

10:05.380 --> 10:07.000
So we're gonna do Christmas,
huh?

10:07.000 --> 10:09.000
But we can scale it back,
alright?

10:09.000 --> 10:11.080
We don't have to have
the open house tomorrow.

10:11.080 --> 10:13.620
Might be good
to see people.

10:13.620 --> 10:14.670
Oh.

10:14.670 --> 10:17.920
Yeah, yeah,
I could use the distraction.

10:20.170 --> 10:21.330
Thanks.

10:22.620 --> 10:24.710
Good looking out, son.

10:24.710 --> 10:26.750
Always, man.

10:30.460 --> 10:32.380
Oh, dry clean only.

10:32.380 --> 10:33.500
I just was wondering

10:33.500 --> 10:34.710
if that was, like,
wash and wear,

10:34.710 --> 10:36.580
but...okay.

10:36.580 --> 10:38.790
♪♪

10:38.790 --> 10:41.120
I've never seen anything
like this before in my life.

10:41.120 --> 10:43.250
I was up all night,
worried about Pops.

10:43.250 --> 10:44.420
Well, then,
you're the only person

10:44.420 --> 10:46.120
who snores
while they're awake.

10:46.120 --> 10:47.670
We need
to get rid of everything

10:47.670 --> 10:49.500
that would remind him
of what happened,

10:49.500 --> 10:51.580
starting
with these jammies

10:51.580 --> 10:52.920
that Lynette bought us,
alright?

10:52.920 --> 10:53.920
We got to lose them.
These?

10:53.920 --> 10:55.330
But they're
the softest things

10:55.330 --> 10:57.380
that have ever
touched my body.
Dre: I don't care.

10:57.380 --> 11:00.460
These and everything else
that will remind him of her

11:00.460 --> 11:02.080
need to go
into the wood chipper.

11:02.080 --> 11:04.420
You finally got me
my wood chipper?

11:04.420 --> 11:05.620
What? No!

11:05.620 --> 11:07.620
Why would I get you
a wood chipper?

11:07.620 --> 11:09.250
You know what? Never mind.
I don't care.

11:09.250 --> 11:10.580
Go get rid
of these things.

11:10.580 --> 11:13.540
Uh...that's
a good fresh start.

11:13.540 --> 11:15.080
Alright,
now we have to figure out

11:15.080 --> 11:17.170
what we're gonna do about
this open house tonight.

11:17.170 --> 11:18.750
We're still having
the open house?

11:18.750 --> 11:20.920
Yeah.
Pops still wants it.

11:20.920 --> 11:24.580
Okay, Dre,
I don't know what I'm doing.

11:24.580 --> 11:26.380
I'm cooking a gumbo

11:26.380 --> 11:28.500
I should've started
four days ago,

11:28.500 --> 11:31.210
and there's some sort of
giant, 10-pound roast

11:31.210 --> 11:32.670
in the oven,

11:32.670 --> 11:34.330
and I don't even know
what kind of meat that is.

11:34.330 --> 11:37.120
You are a doctor, Bow.
Improvise.

11:37.120 --> 11:39.830
That's the one thing
we're not supposed to do.

11:39.830 --> 11:42.000
We are all doing things that
we have never done before.

11:42.000 --> 11:43.750
Did I think
I was gonna have a colonoscopy

11:43.750 --> 11:45.620
before I had my first Christmas
with my daddy?

11:45.620 --> 11:46.790
No!

11:46.790 --> 11:48.750
Bow, miracles are happening
all around us.

11:48.750 --> 11:49.790
Mm-hmm.

11:49.790 --> 11:50.920
Miracles, Bow!

11:50.920 --> 11:53.620
♪♪

11:53.620 --> 11:56.040
So we'd gotten rid
of every trace of Lynette

11:56.040 --> 11:57.420
around the house.

11:57.420 --> 11:59.790
And now it was all about
the good stuff --

11:59.790 --> 12:02.670
watching Laker-Clippers
and opening presents.

12:02.670 --> 12:03.920
He's coming, y'all.

12:03.920 --> 12:06.000
Oh, hey, hey,
how does he look?

12:06.000 --> 12:07.170
I don't know.

12:07.170 --> 12:09.500
Wearing a pastel linen pant
and moving slow.

12:09.500 --> 12:10.670
Looked like Pops.

12:10.670 --> 12:12.500
-Hey, hey, Pops.
-Hey.

12:12.500 --> 12:14.330
-Hey.
-Hey.

12:14.330 --> 12:16.210
Smells like burnt alligator
in here.

12:16.210 --> 12:17.750
That's what it is.

12:17.750 --> 12:18.960
Why don't you come on,
sit down,

12:18.960 --> 12:20.290
and open up a gift

12:20.290 --> 12:22.040
before our guests
start to arrive?

12:22.040 --> 12:23.540
And there's one for you.

12:23.540 --> 12:25.290
"To Pops and L--"
You know what?

12:25.290 --> 12:27.290
Uh, just to Pops.

12:27.290 --> 12:28.380
We don't need that.

12:28.380 --> 12:30.750
Okay.

12:32.040 --> 12:33.500
What is it,
what is it, what is it?

12:33.500 --> 12:35.000
-Yeah.
-Mm-hmm.

12:35.000 --> 12:37.750
-Oh.
-That's a good one.

12:37.750 --> 12:39.750
Oh, an olive-wood
cutting board.

12:39.750 --> 12:40.500
Very nice.

12:40.500 --> 12:41.960
-Pretty.
-Oh.

12:41.960 --> 12:43.880
Dre: Oh, you got
a "Lynette & Earl."

12:43.880 --> 12:45.420
That's, uh --
That's a brand name,

12:45.420 --> 12:47.500
like, uh --
like Black & Decker.

12:47.500 --> 12:48.460
Mm-hmm.
You know what, Pops?

12:48.460 --> 12:49.670
We can open up gifts later,

12:49.670 --> 12:52.500
because the real present
at Christmas is people.

12:52.500 --> 12:53.420
Yes, it is.

12:53.420 --> 12:55.750
Hey, Portal,
call Rhonda.

12:55.750 --> 12:57.500
[ Portal beeps ]

12:57.500 --> 13:00.670
[ Ringing ]

13:00.670 --> 13:02.330
Hey, Portal, answer.

13:02.330 --> 13:04.120
[ Portal beeps ]

13:04.120 --> 13:06.000
-Hey, hey!
-Oh, hey!

13:06.000 --> 13:08.080
-Merry Christmas.
-Hey, family.

13:08.080 --> 13:09.380
Rhonda:
Merry Christmas.

13:09.380 --> 13:11.920
Pops, word on the street
is you got dumped.

13:11.920 --> 13:15.750
Pops: Uh, yeah, yeah,
that -- that happened.
Dre: Rhonda.

13:15.750 --> 13:19.380
Oh, I'm so sorry
to hear that, Pops.

13:19.380 --> 13:20.920
She didn't deserve you
anyway.

13:20.920 --> 13:22.960
Oh, yeah. For sure.

13:22.960 --> 13:25.830
And, you know,
it's Christmas Day,

13:25.830 --> 13:27.880
and I'm surrounded
by the people I love.

13:27.880 --> 13:29.330
Yeah, and Dre.

13:29.330 --> 13:30.460
[ Laughs ]
Okay.

13:30.460 --> 13:31.500
She burned you.
I'll remember that.

13:31.500 --> 13:32.790
I'll remember that.

13:32.790 --> 13:34.380
Dre: I didn't care
how it was happening.

13:34.380 --> 13:35.670
All that mattered is

13:35.670 --> 13:38.250
it seemed like Pops
was coming back to life.

13:38.250 --> 13:39.210
[ Doorbell rings ]

13:39.210 --> 13:40.420
Oh, excuse me.

13:40.420 --> 13:42.120
Yeah?

13:42.120 --> 13:43.710
Hey.

13:43.710 --> 13:45.000
Hey, hey, Doug,
what are you doing here, man?

13:45.000 --> 13:46.000
My Pops can't see you.

13:46.000 --> 13:47.120
Hey, hey, you know,

13:47.120 --> 13:48.420
just because my mom
isn't with your dad

13:48.420 --> 13:50.000
doesn't mean you and I
can't hang out.

13:50.000 --> 13:51.710
Doug, that's exactly
what that means.

13:51.710 --> 13:54.120
But we were gonna go see that
new "Star Wars" together.

13:54.120 --> 13:56.170
Hey, hey, you know what?
Check this, Doug.

13:56.170 --> 13:58.120
You still can, alright?
I hear it's great.

13:58.120 --> 13:59.580
But what I'm trying
to say is,

13:59.580 --> 14:01.040
"These are not the Dres
that you're looking for."

14:01.040 --> 14:03.040
Alright?
Merry Christmas, Doug.

14:03.040 --> 14:05.380
May the Force be with you.
But -- Hey.

14:05.380 --> 14:07.290
So it was
a closed door for Doug

14:07.290 --> 14:09.330
and an open house
for everyone else.

14:09.330 --> 14:11.330
[ Chuckles ] Hey, Janine.
Yeah?

14:11.330 --> 14:12.670
Hominy?

14:12.670 --> 14:14.000
Onion fritter?

14:14.000 --> 14:15.670
Blackened gator?

14:15.670 --> 14:17.330
Thank you, no, no.
No?

14:17.330 --> 14:20.000
No, I'm -- I'm -- I'm full
from those giant shrimp.

14:20.000 --> 14:21.670
Oh, delicious.
Yeah, I-I've never --

14:21.670 --> 14:23.080
never had them
like that before,

14:23.080 --> 14:24.750
you know, with -- with the eyes
and the whiskers

14:24.750 --> 14:26.040
and the...
Yeah.

14:26.040 --> 14:27.670
...and the kind of
still moving around.

14:27.670 --> 14:29.380
There's a lot of fight
in those little guys.

14:29.380 --> 14:30.460
Mm.
Huh?

14:30.460 --> 14:32.670
Makes them tasty.
[ Laughs ]

14:32.670 --> 14:34.460
[ Sighs ]
Hey, you're an old lady.

14:34.460 --> 14:37.000
If you were going to hide $200
in a house like this,

14:37.000 --> 14:38.290
where would you put it?

14:38.290 --> 14:40.290
[ Sighs ]

14:40.290 --> 14:41.380
Wha...

14:41.380 --> 14:43.120
Introduce you
to everybody in here.

14:43.120 --> 14:45.830
Hey, everybody,
this is Cheryl.

14:45.830 --> 14:47.210
Oh, my goodness.

14:47.210 --> 14:48.540
Oh, my goodness.

14:48.540 --> 14:51.000
Is that
what I think it is?

14:51.000 --> 14:52.040
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

14:52.040 --> 14:53.500
Mm. Mwah.

14:53.500 --> 14:55.000
[ Laughs ]

14:55.000 --> 14:58.290
Uh, okay, Pops,
uh, who's this?

14:58.290 --> 15:00.380
This is Cheryl.
She an old friend of mine.

15:00.380 --> 15:02.000
I called her
on the landline.

15:02.000 --> 15:03.290
She picked up.
One ring.

15:03.290 --> 15:04.790
Here we are.
Okay.

15:04.790 --> 15:07.710
She has aroused
my Christmas spirit.

15:07.710 --> 15:09.170
You feel me?
Ah. [ Chuckles ]

15:09.170 --> 15:10.790
That's, uh, gross.

15:10.790 --> 15:13.380
But, uh, glad to see
that you're back.

15:13.380 --> 15:14.670
Alright.
Come on, baby.

15:14.670 --> 15:16.620
Let's get you a drink.
Ooh, okay.

15:16.620 --> 15:17.670
♪♪

15:17.670 --> 15:18.790
Hey, babe, come here.

15:18.790 --> 15:21.290
What?

15:21.290 --> 15:22.500
Look at Pops
over there.

15:24.120 --> 15:26.290
Did you hire that woman
for your father?

15:26.290 --> 15:27.830
No.
Oh.

15:27.830 --> 15:30.830
This is a legit, old-school
Christmas Day booty call.

15:30.830 --> 15:31.830
Wow.

15:31.830 --> 15:33.670
I think Pops
is gonna be okay.

15:33.670 --> 15:34.880
Yeah.

15:34.880 --> 15:36.170
She seems great.

15:36.170 --> 15:38.540
Hey,
can you try the gumbo?

15:38.540 --> 15:42.170
'Cause the spoon is not
supposed to break off

15:42.170 --> 15:43.620
when you're stirring it,
right?

15:43.620 --> 15:45.750
No.
Okay.

15:45.750 --> 15:47.170
♪♪

15:47.170 --> 15:49.380
Eggnog?
What's in it?

15:49.380 --> 15:52.250
Oh, uh, heavy cream,
egg yolks, sugar, and rum.

15:52.250 --> 15:53.880
Mmm.
So I'm drinking cake?
Yeah.

15:53.880 --> 15:55.960
What a fantastic
White idea.

15:55.960 --> 15:57.330
[ Both chuckle ]

15:57.330 --> 15:59.210
Now, um,
what holiday is this?

16:00.170 --> 16:02.000
I got a little something
for you, baby.

16:02.000 --> 16:03.040
Oh.

16:03.040 --> 16:04.170
I hope you like it.

16:05.170 --> 16:06.170
[ Gasps ]

16:06.170 --> 16:08.120
There's a picture of me
inside.

16:08.120 --> 16:10.460
So I'll always be
close to your heart.

16:10.460 --> 16:13.500
It's lovely, Earl,
but jewelry?

16:13.500 --> 16:15.290
What?
You're my girl.

16:15.290 --> 16:17.330
I am?
Mm-hmm.

16:17.330 --> 16:20.120
We haven't seen each other
in a year.

16:20.120 --> 16:21.670
Yes,
but we have something.

16:21.670 --> 16:23.210
Look,
let's get out of here.

16:23.210 --> 16:25.830
Let's go get some ice cream
or elope.

16:25.830 --> 16:27.670
[ Chuckles ]

16:27.670 --> 16:29.960
I think this is moving
a little too fast.

16:29.960 --> 16:31.670
What?
Maybe I should go.

16:31.670 --> 16:33.790
Wait, wait.
You're leaving me?

16:33.790 --> 16:35.000
On Christmas?

16:35.000 --> 16:37.290
I invited you
into my family.

16:37.290 --> 16:39.000
We were supposed to spend
our lives together.

16:39.000 --> 16:40.380
We were supposed
to get married.

16:42.290 --> 16:43.500
She said forever.

16:43.500 --> 16:46.080
I guess forever don't mean
what I thought it meant.

16:46.080 --> 16:49.250
[ Door opens ]
If he wants to get married,
I'm available.

16:49.250 --> 16:51.000
[ Door closes ]
Classic holiday moment.

16:51.000 --> 16:52.920
Want to go get a drink?

16:52.920 --> 16:55.670
I'd love to.
That's okay.

16:55.670 --> 16:57.750
You didn't let me chase you
long enough.

16:57.750 --> 17:00.210
♪♪

17:03.420 --> 17:05.670
♪♪

17:05.670 --> 17:07.500
[ Knock on door,
door opens ]

17:09.330 --> 17:10.500
Hey.

17:10.500 --> 17:12.500
Uh...

17:12.500 --> 17:14.080
I'm sorry, Pops.

17:14.080 --> 17:15.540
We should have canceled
that whole open-house thing.

17:15.540 --> 17:16.710
This is on me.

17:16.710 --> 17:18.540
The open house
didn't make me call Cheryl.

17:18.540 --> 17:20.500
I just can't understand

17:20.500 --> 17:21.710
what went wrong
with Lynette.

17:21.710 --> 17:23.330
Why'd she leave me

17:23.330 --> 17:25.330
after I changed so much
for the better, son?

17:25.330 --> 17:28.120
Hey, Pops,
I can't answer that, man.

17:28.120 --> 17:29.620
Sometimes you do
what's right,

17:29.620 --> 17:30.830
and it still
doesn't work out.

17:30.830 --> 17:33.250
And I still feel like
a damn fool.

17:33.250 --> 17:35.750
I proposed to Lynette
after just three weeks.

17:35.750 --> 17:37.420
I put on the Santa suit.

17:37.420 --> 17:39.080
I read
a Jamaica Kincaid novel.

17:39.080 --> 17:40.670
Mm-hmm.
I mean,
I really believed

17:40.670 --> 17:42.080
that we were
going to be together

17:42.080 --> 17:43.250
for the rest
of our lives.

17:43.250 --> 17:44.670
Pops,
and that's growth.

17:44.670 --> 17:46.500
You loved someone

17:46.500 --> 17:48.620
in a way that
you should love someone.

17:48.620 --> 17:50.670
Like you're never
expecting it to end.

17:50.670 --> 17:52.040
Yeah, but it did end.

17:52.040 --> 17:53.290
Yeah, this one did.

17:53.290 --> 17:54.500
[ Sighs ]

17:54.500 --> 17:58.920
Pops, you being with Lynette
made you a better person.

17:58.920 --> 18:00.710
This Pops gave me

18:00.710 --> 18:02.830
the best Christmas
I've ever had.

18:05.580 --> 18:07.420
Yeah, it was a pretty good
Christmas, though, wasn't it?

18:07.420 --> 18:10.170
[ Chuckles ]
Till I got my ass dumped.

18:10.170 --> 18:12.000
[ Inhales sharply ]
Ooh.

18:12.000 --> 18:14.750
Son, how did I lose my woman
to a guy named Phillip?

18:14.750 --> 18:16.380
If he ain't
in Earth, Wind & Fire,

18:16.380 --> 18:17.420
makes no sense to me.

18:17.420 --> 18:22.920
[ Both laugh ]

18:22.920 --> 18:26.040
Hey, Pops, come back
to the house, man.

18:26.040 --> 18:29.210
The kids are hanging,
Bow's gumbo's almost ready.

18:29.210 --> 18:32.380
Yeah,
I-I think I'm okay.

18:32.380 --> 18:34.500
You sure?
Yeah, I think I'm good.

18:34.500 --> 18:37.210
Listen, I'll probably just
go and find someplace

18:37.210 --> 18:38.500
that's still
serving alcohol.

18:38.500 --> 18:40.670
Of course you will.
Mm.

18:40.670 --> 18:43.290
Well,
you're not missing anything.

18:43.290 --> 18:45.040
That gumbo's probably
not gonna be ready

18:45.040 --> 18:47.250
till tomorrow at the earliest
anyway.

18:49.790 --> 18:51.120
Hey, Pops.

18:53.750 --> 18:55.670
I love you.

18:55.670 --> 19:00.460
♪♪

19:00.460 --> 19:02.120
Love you, too, son.

19:02.120 --> 19:04.710
♪♪

19:04.710 --> 19:06.380
Ah, it's not
in the closet.

19:06.380 --> 19:07.830
Not in here, either.

19:07.830 --> 19:09.250
[ Grunts ]

19:10.670 --> 19:12.540
You tossed my room?

19:12.540 --> 19:14.330
Well, we asked
the Magic 8-Ball

19:14.330 --> 19:16.330
if the money
was in Junior's room,

19:16.330 --> 19:17.830
and it said,
"You can rely on it."

19:17.830 --> 19:19.500
That's the best lead
we have.

19:19.500 --> 19:21.170
Help me pull
this carpet up.

19:23.000 --> 19:26.670
♪♪

19:26.670 --> 19:28.040
Is that
what I think it is?

19:28.040 --> 19:29.830
Devante found the money.

19:29.830 --> 19:31.880
It would be so easy
to take it from him.

19:31.880 --> 19:33.210
It'd be like taking candy
from him.

19:33.210 --> 19:34.420
[ Sighs ] We can't.

19:34.420 --> 19:35.830
He found it
fair and square.

19:35.830 --> 19:39.170
But we can trade.

19:39.170 --> 19:42.040
Devante,
you want the shiny?

19:42.040 --> 19:44.080
The crinkly?

19:44.080 --> 19:47.000
So your big brother
can put gas in his car?

19:47.920 --> 19:49.540
No, Devante,
don't do it.

19:49.540 --> 19:50.960
What?

19:50.960 --> 19:52.040
Yes!

19:52.380 --> 19:53.670
What?
[ Chuckles ]

19:53.670 --> 19:54.790
Well played.

19:54.790 --> 19:56.170
I would've done
the same thing.

19:56.170 --> 19:57.670
Me, too.

19:57.670 --> 19:59.670
That bag is so shiny.

19:59.670 --> 20:00.710
♪♪

20:03.420 --> 20:07.080
♪ Silent night, holy night ♪

20:07.080 --> 20:09.540
Ruby: So, I guess I know
how you're doing.

20:09.540 --> 20:13.120
I can't lie,
I've been better.

20:13.120 --> 20:15.000
♪ All is bright ♪

20:15.000 --> 20:16.330
I'm sorry to hear that,
Earl.

20:16.330 --> 20:18.420
♪ 'Round yon virgin ♪

20:18.420 --> 20:20.670
Thanks for coming, Ruby.
Ah, it's nothing.

20:20.670 --> 20:22.790
There were three heart attacks
on the ship

20:22.790 --> 20:24.830
before it even left
the Long Beach Harbor.

20:24.830 --> 20:27.000
Damn.
You know,
young people think

20:27.000 --> 20:30.330
they've got the market
cornered on heartbreak,

20:30.330 --> 20:32.670
but at our age,

20:32.670 --> 20:35.000
stings like a son of a bitch,
doesn't it?

20:35.000 --> 20:37.540
I thought I was done
with all that.
Mm.

20:37.540 --> 20:40.290
How is it possible
it hurts more now?

20:40.290 --> 20:41.380
Well,
when you're young,

20:41.380 --> 20:43.000
you still have
your life ahead of you,

20:43.000 --> 20:45.420
but now you don't know

20:45.420 --> 20:47.710
how many more opportunities
you're gonna have at love.

20:47.710 --> 20:49.790
I'm-a need
another drink.

20:49.790 --> 20:51.670
Hey, Earl, hey.
Huh?

20:53.250 --> 20:55.670
It'll happen.

20:55.670 --> 20:57.920
You're too good of a man
for it not to.

20:57.920 --> 20:59.080
♪ Glories stream... ♪

20:59.080 --> 21:04.000
But, Earl, you do know...

21:04.000 --> 21:05.880
part of you
deserves this.

21:05.880 --> 21:08.710
♪ Heavenly hosts
sing Alleluia ♪

21:08.710 --> 21:11.500
Uh-huh. Yeah, yeah.

21:11.500 --> 21:13.170
Yeah, come on.
Help me with this pie.

21:13.170 --> 21:14.170
I can't eat it all.

21:14.170 --> 21:15.670
Oh, I shouldn't.

21:15.670 --> 21:17.500
Merry Christmas, Earl.

21:17.500 --> 21:18.880
Merry Christmas, Ruby.

21:18.880 --> 21:23.330
♪ Christ the Savior is born ♪
